<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 01 at 5:49PM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Jackson, southern Harmon, northwestern Foard, northwestern Wilbarger
and Hardeman Counties through 615 PM CDT...
At 548 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southwest of Goodlett, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 to 45 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Quanah, Eldorado, Goodlett and Lazare.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
